b'{"data_headers":{"result_code":1},"data":{"information":{"article_id":2138,"category_name":"Events","pr_category_id":"4","title_name":"A New Raid Event, Rage of Chronos, Is Now Live!","message":"<div>Up to four players with four adventurers each (up to 16 adventurers in total!) can battle together in the Rage of Chronos raid event, which began on <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1619589600\\"><\/span>. Take on event-specific quests to defeat the raid boss with no elemental attunement and earn rewards!<\/div><div><br><\/div><div><img src=\\"https:\/\/dragalialost.akamaized.net\/attached\/information\/images\/914d52cff9aa24b7693f9181e642fbc5.png\\"><\/div><div>One day, the vampire princess Vania appears on the Halidom&#39;s doorstep seeking bloodkin. At her side is Chronos, a dragon who once caused the prince and friends much anguish. After a war god dispatched by the heavens descends to offer his aid, it falls to our heroes to pass judgment on the artificial dragon that trifles with time&#39;s laws!<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>This event&#39;s theme song is &quot;Sample Answer&quot; by Megumi Ogata.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Event Duration<\/div><div><span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1619589600\\"><\/span> to <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1620626399\\"><\/span><\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Nightmare and Omega difficulties will unlock on <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1620021600\\"><\/span>.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Note: If the event ends while you are in a quest, the quest will continue until the results have been determined. You will be able to earn rewards according to the results of the quest.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Reward Availability Period<\/div><div><span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1619589600\\"><\/span> to <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1621231199\\"><\/span><\/div><div>Note: You will be able to perform blazon summons and obtain emblem rewards during this period.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Epilogue<\/div><div>The epilogue for this event will unlock on <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1620626400\\"><\/span>.<\/div><div>Note: To view the epilogue, you must complete episode 6 of the event story.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Epilogue Availability<\/div><div><span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1620626400\\"><\/span> to <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1621231199\\"><\/span><\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Event Perks<\/div><div>While this event is active, adventurers recruited through the main story (excluding versions from summon showcases, events, or other sources) and newly added featured adventurers from summon showcases available during this event will have special abilities that activate in quests for this event. The numerical values of an adventurer&#39;s event perks depend on if they belong to the former or the latter category. See Event Perks on the main event screen in-game for more information.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Raid Battles<\/div><div>Raid battles are co-op battles where up to four teams (up to 16 adventurers in total) can cooperate against a raid boss together! To participate in a raid battle, you must either create a room as the host or join a room as a guest.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u30fbAs a Host:<\/div><div>Creating a room requires otherworld fragments and getherwings. You can obtain otherworld fragments from boss battles.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u30fbAs a Guest:<\/div><div>Joining a room requires otherworld fragments and getherwings. You must have unlocked the respective difficulty to participate in a raid battle.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Extra Raid Battles<\/div><div>This event does not include Extra Raid Battles.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Roar of the Mad Cyclone<\/div><div>To challenge this solo-play-exclusive quest, you must unlock it by clearing the raid battle on Expert difficulty. Playing this quest requires cyclone bindings instead of stamina. You can obtain cyclone bindings from endeavors and the Grand Bounty. Clear this quest to earn a large amount of various emblems and peregrine blazons.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Omega Difficulty<\/div><div>To challenge Omega difficulty, you must clear the raid battle on Nightmare difficulty and complete episode 6 of the event story. Additionally, to unlock Omega difficulty, you must collect three omega keys. You can obtain one omega key from each type of emblem rewards: bronze emblems, silver emblems, and gold emblems.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u30fbOmega Level 1 (Solo)<\/div><div>This quest is for solo play only. It will unlock when you clear the raid battle on Nightmare difficulty and complete episode 6 of the event story.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u30fbOmega Level 1 (Raid)<\/div><div>This quest is for co-op play only and will unlock when you clear Omega Level 1 (Solo).<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u30fbOmega Level 2 (Solo)<\/div><div>This quest is for solo play only and will unlock when you clear Omega Level 1 (Raid).<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u30fbOmega Level 2 (Raid)<\/div><div>This quest is for co-op play only and will unlock when you clear Omega Level 2 (Solo).<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u30fbOmega Level 3 (Solo)<\/div><div>This quest is for solo play only and will unlock when you clear Omega Level 2 (Raid).<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u30fbOmega Level 3 (Raid)<\/div><div>This quest is for co-op play only and will unlock when you clear Omega Level 3 (Solo).<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Raid Boosts<\/div><div>When you clear raid battles, you&#39;ll be able to get raid boosts, which power up adventurers for this event only.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Raid boosts you obtain will stack and only apply to your team. The maximum effects you can achieve with raid boosts are described below.<\/div><div>\\u30fbDamage +100%<\/div><div>\\u30fbHP +50%<\/div><div>\\u30fbShapeshift Prep +25%<\/div><div>\\u30fbDragon Time +50%<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>The number of raid boosts you can obtain by clearing a single quest varies depending on the difficulty. There are also special rare raid boosts. In this event, you will not be able to obtain rare raid boosts from boss battles.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Raid battle co-op rooms will display each team&#39;s boosted might, which factors in the increased power from raid boosts. Boosted might does not affect the might required to start a quest.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Blazon Summons<\/div><div>Complete boss battles and raid battles to obtain peregrine blazons. Blazons collected can be used for blazon summoning to get orichalcum and other rewards.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>After obtaining orichalcum, you can reset the contents available. From the 5th reset onward, you must accept all rewards before you can reset the contents available.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Emblems<\/div><div>You can obtain various rewards based on the total number of emblems you gather during the event.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Event Endeavors<\/div><div>Two types of event endeavors will be available during the event: Daily and Limited.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Notes:<\/div><div>1. During raid battles, you will only recover 1\/4 of the amount of HP from certain skills and abilities.<\/div><div>2. Players must have completed up to Chapter 2 \/ 2-1 (Normal) of the main campaign to participate in event quests.<\/div><div>3. Players must have completed up to Chapter 2 \/ 2-1 (Normal) of the main campaign to play co-op.<\/div><div>4. You will not be able to use blazons, emblems, otherworld gems, or otherworld fragments obtained in this event in future events.<\/div><div>5. For details concerning this raid event, check the Help section on the raid event&#39;s top page in the game.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Thank you for playing Dragalia Lost.<\/div>","start_time":1619589600,"prev_article_id":"2145","next_article_id":"2159","image_path":"https:\/\/dragalialost.akamaized.net\/attached\/information\/images\/914d52cff9aa24b7693f9181e642fbc5.png","update_time":1619510291}}}'